JODI SCHOTTENFELD-ROAMES: MOL 350 is really 
designed to prepare students as juniors

00:00:04.810 --> 00:00:07.420
to be able to walk into
their labs as seniors,

00:00:07.420 --> 00:00:09.850
perform their senior thesis,
already have the ability

00:00:09.850 --> 00:00:11.040
to read primary literature.

00:00:11.040 --> 00:00:13.300
So they work with
drosophila and they're

00:00:13.300 --> 00:00:15.391
focusing on the tracheal
system of flies.

00:00:15.391 --> 00:00:17.890
It's incredibly analogous to
the vertebrate vascular system.

00:00:17.890 --> 00:00:20.098
They're doing what's called
amino fluorescence, where

00:00:20.098 --> 00:00:21.970
they're tagging
certain proteins,

00:00:21.970 --> 00:00:23.860
and then they're using
a microscope called

00:00:23.860 --> 00:00:26.940
a confocal microscope so that
they can visualize the stains

00:00:26.940 --> 00:00:28.630
that they're looking at.

